title: Main Challenge: Spicy Southern Collard Greens with Sweet Maple Cornbread
summary: Main Challenge: Spicy Southern Collard Greens with Sweet Maple Cornbread is a Southern recipe that serves 8. One portion of this dish contains roughly 18g of protein, 22g of fat, and a total of 442 calories. For $1.6 per serving, this recipe covers 32% of your daily requirements of vitamins and minerals. A couple people really liked this side dish. A mixture of onion, cornmeal, flour, and a handful of other ingredients are all it takes to make this recipe so tasty. This recipe from Foodnetwork has 31 fans. From preparation to the plate, this recipe takes around 1 hour and 20 minutes. All things considered, we decided this recipe deserves a spoonacular score of 87%. This score is spectacular. If you like this recipe, you might also like recipes such as Main Challenge: Spicy Southern Collard Greens with Sweet Maple Cornbread, Spicy Southern Collard Greens, and Perfect Southern Greens (Kale, Beet, Collard Greens, Mustard).

winePairing.pairingText: Southern works really well with Riesling, Sparkling Wine, and Zinfandel. In general, there are a few rules that will help you pair wine with southern food. Food-friendly riesling or sparkling white wine will work with many fried foods, while zinfandel is great with barbecued fare. The Engel Wines Riesling - Kosher with a 5 out of 5 star rating seems like a good match. It costs about 20 dollars per bottle.

instructions: Heat the olive oil in a large pot over medium-high heat. Add the pork pieces and brown on both sides, about 6 to 8 minutes. Add the onion, cut sides down, and brown, about 5 to 6 minutes. Stir in the chicken broth. Season with chili flakes, salt, vinegar and garlic powder. Bring to a boil, then turn down the heat to a simmer. Adjust seasoning, if desired. Add the collard greens and garlic cloves, stir to combine and cover. Cook until greens are tender, approximately 35 to 45 minutes. Remove the onion halves, garlic cloves, pork pieces, for better presentation. Transfer the greens to a serving bowl.                          Heat the oven to 375 degrees F. Coat an 8 by 8-inch baking pan with cooking spray.                          In a large bowl, whisk together all the ingredients except the butter and pour into the pan. Bake for 18 to 20 minutes, until the cornbread is lightly golden brown.                          Once baked, remove from the oven and brush with butter. Serve immediately.

steps.step: Heat the olive oil in a large pot over medium-high heat.
Add the pork pieces and brown on both sides, about 6 to 8 minutes.

Add the onion, cut sides down, and brown, about 5 to 6 minutes. Stir in the chicken broth. Season with chili flakes, salt, vinegar and garlic powder. Bring to a boil, then turn down the heat to a simmer. Adjust seasoning, if desired.
Add the collard greens and garlic cloves, stir to combine and cover. Cook until greens are tender, approximately 35 to 45 minutes.
Remove the onion halves, garlic cloves, pork pieces, for better presentation.
Transfer the greens to a serving bowl.
Heat the oven to 375 degrees F. Coat an 8 by 8-inch baking pan with cooking spray.
In a large bowl, whisk together all the ingredients except the butter and pour into the pan.
Bake for 18 to 20 minutes, until the cornbread is lightly golden brown.
Once baked, remove from the oven and brush with butter.
